&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Zone 5 Technologies, we&#39;re redefining what&#39;s possible in unmanned aircraft systems. Our team of engineers and innovators is developing cutting-edge autonomous solutions that push the boundaries of UAS technology - solving complex challenges that matter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re building the future of UAS capabilities, and we&#39;re looking for exceptional talent to join us. If you&#39;re driven by hard problems, energized by rapid innovation, and ready to make an impact on next-generation flight systems, you belong here.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Developmental Test/Environmental Test Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Testing, Validation &amp;amp; MIL-STD-810 - or equivalent - Design Integration)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Zone 5 Technologies, LLC is seeking a highly skilled &lt;strong&gt;Environmental Qualification &amp;amp; Design Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; to lead the environmental testing, validation, and design integration of advanced counter-drone drone and missile systems for U.S. Department of Defense programs. This role requires a deep understanding of &lt;strong&gt;MIL-STD-810&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;EMI/EMC&lt;/strong&gt;, and missile systems—blending hands-on test execution with early-phase design input to ensure our platforms perform in the most demanding operational environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, author, and execute detailed &lt;strong&gt;environmental test plans&lt;/strong&gt; in compliance with &lt;strong&gt;MIL-STD-810&lt;/strong&gt; and related military standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with design engineering teams to integrate test-derived insights into hardware architecture, material selection, and packaging to improve reliability and survivability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate environmental qualification needs into&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;design guidelines&lt;/strong&gt; and drive early-phase design reviews to ensure environmental readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct and oversee testing across critical environments, including&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;shock, vibration, temperature, humidity, rain, and sand/dust&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and support &lt;strong&gt;EMI/EMC testing&lt;/strong&gt;, including collaboration with external labs and internal electrical teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead &lt;strong&gt;test setup planning&lt;/strong&gt;, including harnessing, fixturing, instrumentation, and data acquisition strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as primary technical interface for &lt;strong&gt;third-party test houses&lt;/strong&gt;—coordinating logistics, validating setup integrity, and ensuring test fidelity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply knowledge of&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;missile systems&lt;/strong&gt; and counter-UAS platforms to guide realistic and mission-relevant test planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ideal Candidate Profile:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A minimum of 5 years&lt;/strong&gt; of relevant experience in aerospace, defense, or high-reliability systems engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct hands-on expertise in &lt;strong&gt;MIL-STD-810&lt;/strong&gt; environmental testing, with working knowledge of &lt;strong&gt;DO-160&lt;/strong&gt; and/or related military/industry standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in identifying root cause failure and incorporating insights into early design phases to ensure success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of both &lt;strong&gt;mechanical and electrical systems&lt;/strong&gt;, including familiarity with power/harnessing, enclosures, and electronics packaging under extreme conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with test instrumentation, vibration tables, thermal chambers, and data collection tools.&lt;/li&gt;
